<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-669-292  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 669 292.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telecommunications  July 1990 v24 n7 p26(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>An evolution path to ATM. (asynchronous transfer mode-basedbroadband ISDN architectures)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tat, Thang Nguyen; Fisher, David; Berglund, Anders.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A flexible network architecture allowing a smooth transition toasynchronous mode transfer (ATM)-based broadband ISDN has beendeveloped by the Atmospheric project, a part of the European RACEprogram.andP;  The architecture uses building blocks interconnectedusing standardized interfaces combined in different configurationsrepresenting stages in the evolution from current networks.andO;External interfaces handle synchronous G.708 digital hierarchy(SDH) structures and SDH framed and unframed broadband ISDNuser/network interfaces finalized by the CCITT Study Group XVIII.andO;Functional groups handling switching and/or multiplexing tasks ina hybrid network environment were identified, and each of the fourtypes of network nodes were created using the building blocks:customer nodes, local area multiplexer nodes, remote units andmain network nodes.andP;  The network building blocks, trunkmultiplexer, interface block switch, ATM switch and other keycomponents are described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Network ArchitectureISDNResearch and DevelopmentNew TechniqueBroadbandAsynchronousDigital communications.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Implementation groups. (chart)Network termination 1. (chart)Exchange termination. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>